    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Enrich company profiles with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API automatically for Conversational AI (01157)\n\n**Pattern:** Data Enrichment · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nEnrich company profiles with HubSpot and HTTP / REST API automatically for Conversational AI (01157). It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual conversational ai is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Read Pending Queue (HubSpot) → Normalize Request Payload → Work in Batches → Aggregate Batch Results → Mark Completed in Google Sheets → Enrich with Reference Data → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to data enrichment without manual effort\n- Anyone automating conversational ai in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; HubSpot private-app token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "f13e19ee-526c-0b2e-e015-18a27c0fe0ac",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "7a3c59c8-d853-2766-d09d-e1086f4e07bc",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "a7931fb5-cd1d-2e8b-0ad1-b4764d491b7d",
      "name": "⏱ Rate limiting"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your conversational ai process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
